issue.title: log odds ratio for McNemar Test producing NaNs
issue.body:
Here is a reproducible example:

``` r

# preparing data
dat <- data.frame(
  `1st survey` = c('Approve', 'Approve', 'Disapprove', 'Disapprove'),
  `2nd survey` = c('Approve', 'Disapprove', 'Approve', 'Disapprove'),
  `Counts` = c(794, 150, 86, 570),
  check.names = FALSE
)

# getting log odds ratio
jmv::contTablesPaired(
  data = dat,
  rows = '1st survey',
  cols = '2nd survey',
  counts = 'Counts',
  exact = TRUE
)
#> 
#>  PAIRED SAMPLES CONTINGENCY TABLES
#> 
#>  Contingency Tables                               
#>  ------------------------------------------------ 
#>    1st survey    Approve    Disapprove    Total   
#>  ------------------------------------------------ 
#>    Approve           794           150      944   
#>    Disapprove         86           570      656   
#>    Total             880           720     1600   
#>  ------------------------------------------------ 
#> 
#> 
#>  McNemar Test                                      
#>  ------------------------------------------------- 
#>                            Value    df    p        
#>  ------------------------------------------------- 
#>    <U+03C7>Â²                       17.4     1    < .001   
#>    Log odds ratio exact      NaN                   
#>    N                        1600                   
#>  -------------------------------------------------
```
